description:
Our home is a lovely 2 story, 3 bedroom house near many attractions; Brooklyn College, King's Theater, Prospect Park, Brooklyn Museum, Brooklyn Children's Museum, Brooklyn Botanical Garden, Prospect Park Zoo, Brooklyn Central Library, & Grand Army Plaza.

You’ll love our place because of the light, bright open spaces, ample storage, clean simple midcentury furnishings, and quaint block. Our place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and big groups.

hosts.about: Hi, I'm Tasha; from Miami originally but now a proud new yorker!  I've lived in NYC for 17 years. I've lived in the East & West Villages, Lower East Side, Brooklyn and for the last few months in this great apt right on the border of Harlem and Morningside Heights. This neighborhood has everything you could ever want: nightlife, great food, shopping, Central Park, Columbia University and quick access to subways and sightseeing. My husband works for an arts organization in Hudson (upstate) NY so we are there much of the time. We'd love to have you stay in our clean, well-appointed home when we're not here! We'll give you the lowdown on all of our favorite spots - from legendary pastry shops to secret speakeasys - and know that you'll love our home and neighborhood just as much as we do. When we're not working we love to travel (we went to India on our honeymoon and have been obsessed ever since), cook (whatever looks delicious at the greenmarket and lots of asian dishes), read, write, hike and scuba dive (whenever possible which never feels like enough!)  If this is your first time visiting NYC or if it's your 'old familiar' - you can't find a better neighborhood to stay in. Feel free to send me a message and I'll respond right away. We look forward to hosting you on your travels. Cheers! Tasha & DW
